On Mon, 18 Jan 1999, Greg Smart wrote:
| For more information, see www.Linux.ORG and www.LinuxResources.com.
This should be something more like:
For more information, see <
http://www.Linux.ORG
> and
<
http://www.LinuxResources.com
>. 
I feel citing the references as complete URLs is important, especially if
this will be electronically published. Some Usenet newsreaders (among other
things) will not find the web site reference if it is not a URL (as opposed
to a hostname that just happens to begin with 'www'). 
